@node "HardAdditional" "The CardReader Specifications - Additional Information"
@toc "Hardware"

@{MS "The CardReader Specifications - Additional Information"}

              Memory Card Connector@{par}
         ______________________________@{par}
        |                              |@{par}
        | [#][#][#]  [#][#][#]  [#][#] |   (front view)@{par}
        |______________________________|@{par}
 pin No.   9  7  6    5  4  3    2  1@{par}


   pin  signal@{par}
   No.   name  direction  logic      function@{par}
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------@{par}
   1    DAT      in      positive   Serial Output data(open drain)@{par}
   2    CMD      out     positive   Serial Command data@{par}
   3    +7V      -       -          +7.6V CD-ROM Drive Power@{par}
   4    GND      -       -          Signal Ground@{par}
   5    +3V      -       -          +3.5V System Power@{par}
   6    SEL-     out     negative   pad/memory select@{par}
   7    CLK-     out     negative   Serial Clock@{par}
   9    ACK-     in      negative   Acknowledge(open drain)@{par}
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------@{par}

As you can see the MemoryCard needs two different voltages. I know this is not allways true, but I
checked out four 15 block cards and 3 of them need 7.6V. This voltage requires an @{"external powersupply" link "FAQSExternalV"},
so why not create a full compatible card reader!


@{b}The LM317 is a standard element. The additional characters can be ignored. You can use a LM317T
as well as a LM317Q oder LM317LZ.@{ub}


                   .-----.@{par}
                   |LM   |  1 - Adjust@{par}
   text side of    |317  |  2 - Out@{par}
   LM317           |     |  3 - In@{par}
                   `+-+-+'@{par}
                    | | | @{par}
                   1 2 3  @{par}

      .-------.               3.6V (pin 5)   |    7.6V (pin 3)@{par}
---in-| LM317 |-+-out---      R1    R2       |    R1    R2@{par}
      `---+---' |             270   470      |    270   1370@{par}
          |     R1            330   560      |    330   1680@{par}
      adj |     |             390   680      |    390   2000@{par}
          `-----+             470   820      |    470   2400@{par}
                |             560    1k      |    560   2800@{par}
                R2                           |@{par}
                |                            |@{par}
                |                            |@{par}
              GROUND@{par}

For more information of LM317 check www.national.com and get correct PDF-files.


@{b}@{"External powersupply" link "FAQSExternalV"} voltage should be about 9V-18V if you want to get
7.6V.@{ub}

