@node "SettDriv" "MCControl - Preferences/Driver"
@toc "Sett"

@{MS "Driver"}

This gadget specifies the hardware used for reading MemoryCards.@{par}

If you build my @{"parallel port" link "HardPara"} hardware then @{b}"ParallelPort.mcm"@{ub} is the right
driver. If there are any problems, then try the slower version named @{b}"ParallelPortSlow.mcm"@{ub}! If
MCControl reports that there is no compatible hardware found, then your hardware based on the first
version. Use the @{b}"ParallelPortClassic.mcm"@{ub} driver or @{"update" link "FAQSHardUpdate"} you hardware
(very simple)!@{par}

If your reader is designed to work on the @{"disk port" link "HardDisk"}, then you should use the "DiskPort.mcm"! Again,
if there are any problems, then try the slower version @{b}"DiskPortSlow.mcm"@{ub} for slower timing.@{par}

The @{"DexDrive.mcm" link "FAQSDexDrive"} is a driver for the commercial @{"DexDrive" link "FAQSDexDrive"}!@{par}

The @{"PSXPort.mcm" link "FAQSPSXPort"} is a driver for the commercial PSXPort hardware.@{par}

The 30 Block (MultiPage) RamCard driver (@{b}"RamCard.mcm"@{ub}) is only an example for development. There
for the sourcecodes are included. This driver may be useful if you want to use MCControl without a
card reader hardware. I use it for programming MCControl without the need of reading and writing
real memorycards.

@endnode
