@node "SettHeEd" "MCControl - Preferences//Hex Editor"
@toc "Sett"

@{MS "Hex Editor"}

This gadget allows to setup an external hex editor. This is required when using the
@{"Hex Editor..." link "MenuMultEdit"} menu item. By default "FileX %s" is used. FileX is a very
good file editor and can be found in Aminet. Please note that FileX is Shareware and you should pay
the author when using it.@{par}

"%s" is used as place holder for the file name of the save game.

@{b}Important:@{ub}@{par}Many hex tools are disconnecting themself from the CLI. MCControl is
unable to detect program if the user is exiting the editor. This is the reason MCControl
is going to sleep until the savegame is written.@{par}

If you're quiting the editor without changing the file MCControl stays asleep. Use the
workbench or any other tool to delete the temp file in the "T:" directory to wake up
MCControl.@{par}

@endnode
